* The Employee Participation Program and training to ensure that all employees and contractors working on and around the processes are aware of the hazards, can perform their job duties correctly and safely;

* Procedures for Hot Work, Confined Space Entry, line breaks and other potentially hazardous processes and training in those procedures so that job duties can be performed safely;

* Contractor Safety Program to ensure that all contractors performing work for Spoetzl Brewery are qualified to perform job duties correctly and safely;

* Management of Change and Pre-startup Safety Reviews to ensure that changes are documented, analyzed and kept within the design basis; 

* Incident Investigation procedures that provide method to investigate each incident, including "near misses" to determine root causes and make needed safety improvements.



The program also provides for the required:

* Process Hazard Analyses to evaluate the chemical and process hazards and to determine safeguards that could be added; 

* Compliance Audits to ensure that Process Safety Management requirements are met or exceeded and to address findings promptly; 

* Mechanical Integrity inspections to determine condition of process equipment so that deficiencies can be identified and corrected.



D. Five Year Accident History



Within the past five years, the Spoetzl Brewery has not had any accidental releases that resulted in injuries or property damage or negative environmental impact. The plant has maintained an excellent safety record throughout its operating history with no major anhydrous ammonia releases that could have had adverse effects on the employees, the public, property, or the environment.



